00:08:16,062 --> 00:08:21,584
So it's a little jargony, but dependency is work that your team requires from another

143
00:08:21,644 --> 00:08:23,725
team in order to complete your features.

144
00:08:24,806 --> 00:08:28,068
It's normally hidden work, hard to track.

145
00:08:28,088 --> 00:08:32,830
Sometimes you just might have a stomachache and you're just thinking, oh, there's something

146
00:08:32,890 --> 00:08:34,171
we need from some other team.

147
00:08:34,211 --> 00:08:38,293
I don't know what it is, but I don't feel like we can complete our work.

148
00:08:39,694 --> 00:08:45,997
So dependency is a thing that calls out when you are dependent upon another team.

149
00:08:47,417 --> 00:08:50,379
Textbook agile scrum teams don't have dependencies,

150
00:08:51,119 --> 00:08:57,802
but unified experience teams building experiences at scale like Destiny do.

151
00:08:57,822 --> 00:09:00,763
So it can be overwhelming. How do you sort this out?

