00:18:02,670 --> 00:18:05,391
Team layer, program layer would be an area or a feature

292
00:18:05,851 --> 00:18:06,271
in the game.

293
00:18:06,331 --> 00:18:08,892
Destiny franchise would be the actual release.

294
00:18:10,512 --> 00:18:14,033
So at the team layer, scrum teams are the atom.

295
00:18:14,693 --> 00:18:17,273
They work for the most part in two-week increments,

296
00:18:17,373 --> 00:18:19,334
sprints, and deliver user stories.

297
00:18:20,314 --> 00:18:22,134
The first generation scrum cannon

298
00:18:23,308 --> 00:18:25,950
focused almost exclusively on this layer,

299
00:18:26,030 --> 00:18:29,233
describing the practices, roles, rituals, exhaustive literature.

300
00:18:29,253 --> 00:18:30,554
You just, you know, look up Scrum,

301
00:18:30,574 --> 00:18:33,297
you'll see a lot of information about this team layer.

302
00:18:34,878 --> 00:18:36,499
It has time box iterations,

303
00:18:36,559 --> 00:18:38,581
we use at Bungie two-week increments.

304
00:18:39,742 --> 00:18:42,264
But what I was really interested in is in the program layer.

305
00:18:43,325 --> 00:18:45,447
So I asked some SAFe experts, I said,

306
00:18:45,507 --> 00:18:47,689
is there, you know, is there a ritual in SAFe

